The paper discusses the issue of adversarial examples in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves analyzing feature attributions, which is a technique commonly used in the field of explainable AI (XAI) and could potentially fall under the category of cs.CR (cryptography and security). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-layer feature attributions, which could also relate to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
